  "prompt": "How do I get job in software testing as a fresher?",
  "response": "Here are steps to get a job in software testing as a fresher:\n\n1. Educational Qualification\n- Basic degree in Computer Science/IT\n- Engineering degree preferred\n- MCA/BCA can also work\n\n2. Technical Skills\n- Learn manual testing fundamentals\n- Learn test case writing\n- Understand testing types\n- Learn basic programming\n- Familiarize with testing tools like:\n  - Selenium\n  - JIRA\n  - TestComplete\n  - QTP/UFT\n\n3. Certifications\n- ISTQB Foundation Level\n- CSTE\n- CTFL\n- Selenium certification\n\n4. Learning Platforms\n- Udemy\n- Coursera\n- YouTube tutorials\n- Online testing courses\n\n5. Skill Development\n- Learn SQL\n- Basic programming languages\n- Understanding of SDLC\n- Knowledge of testing methodologies\n\n6. Job Search Strategies\n- Create LinkedIn profile\n- Update resume highlighting skills\n- Apply on job portals\n- Attend campus placements\n- Apply for internships\n- Network with professionals\n\n7. Interview Preparation\n- Practice common interview questions\n- Prepare technical and HR round answers\n- Develop communication skills\n\n8. Entry-level Roles\n- Junior Tester\n- Test Engineer\n- Quality Assurance Trainee",
